title: Vittoria Eastern States Cup Thunder Mountain Box East Coast Showdown D
description:
VITTORIA Eastern States Cup DH Series Plan:
VITTORIA ESC races are sanctioned by USA Cycling.
VITTORIA ESC is an USAC Eastern Regional DH Championship Series
VITTORIA ESC features 5 USA Cycling State DH Championships.

USAC Annual or Day License is Required:
A current annual or day USAC license is required to practice and race.
USA Cycling Day Licenses are available at all event registrations for $10/Race.
Annual licenses are $75 for adults and available online at: www.usacycling.org

VITTORIA ESC Number Plates:
All Racers must use a 2017 VITTORIA ESC Number Plate anytime they are on course including their race run and practice. Only Racers with VITTORIA ESC Number Plates are allowed on the Race Course.
ESC number plates are available on the ESC website or at every race for $10.00 each.
These plates can be reused by racers at all 2017 VITTORIA ESC races.
Modifications will/can result is disqualification. Lettering/Logos MUST be 100% Intact. NO CUTS!!

Category Upgrades/Downgrades MUST be approved by USA Cycling:
50% of Points will carry over to the new class when a racer upgrades or downgrades their class.
VITTORIA ESC Series Race Podium:
Top 5 in every class make the podium
1st, 2nd and 3rd in every class receive Custom Eastern States Cup Podium Medals and Sponsor Prizes
4th and 5th place receive great products from Euroline Motorex
Venues may enhance prize packages with prizes.
State Champions in every class will receive Custom VITTORIA ESC State Championship Socks and USAC State Medals.

VITTORIA ESC DH Pro Race Payouts:
Cash Awards to Men and Women Pro/Open at each race $500-$200-$100 for 1st-2nd-3rd.
Racers MUST be present at the Series Final Award Ceremonies or at the Race Award Ceremony to Receive Awards and/or Cash Payouts!





DOWNHILL CLASSES

Open 50+ (cat 1/2/3)
Male Amateur 40+ (cat 2/3)
Male Amateur 30-39 (cat 2/3)

Male Expert 40+ (cat1)
Male Expert 30-39 (cat1)
Male Expert 19-29 (cat1)
Male Expert  15-18 (cat1)
Female Pro/Expert Open (pro and cat1)
Male Pro (pro)

VITTORIA ESC DH Series Championship Qualifications:
Series Finals at Mount Snow is for double points
No minimum number of races needed to qualify for DH Series Championship Standings
Top 6 results by points towards the Championship
Any ties will be broken by placement in the series final at Mount Snow
Racers MUST be present at Series Finals Awards to Receive Awards or Cash Payouts!

Vittoria ESC DH Series USAC Regional Championship Awards
Male DH Pro $1500 $500 $250 $150 $100
Female Pro/Expert Open (pro and cat1) $1500 $500 $250 $150 $100

BOX COMPONENTS SHOWDOWNS
The “BOX Showdown” weekends will feature both Enduro and Down Hill races at the largest resorts on our schedule. BOX Components and the ESC will present high end prizing for the top three men and women that race both Enduro and Downhill during the weekend.
RACERS MUST REGISTER AT THE ENDURO TIMING DESK PRIOR TO THE START OF THE FIRST RACE OF THE EVENT TO BE CONSIDERED FOR BOX EAST COAST SHOWDOWN POINTS AND PRIZES

title: USAC Regional Talent ID Road Camp (UMass Amherst))
Dusk to Dawn
description:
We’re riding mixed-terrain in the dark.  All night.  It's that simple; it's just not easy.

This ride is truly like no other ride we've found.  This is out third annual mixed-terrain event that rolls from sun to sun.

Own the night.

http://www.overlandbasecamp.cc/dusk-to-dawn-ride-2017/
course:
Dusk to Dawn offers three ride divisions:

Continuous Solo:  This division rolls all night long - continuously for the full 90-miles, with a few refueling stops along the way - including the Big Fire at about 55-miles.
Camp Out:  This division rides about 55-miles to the Big Fire stop and then camps out for the evening.  Once the sun rises - or anytime before 10 am - you hop in the van or ride home on 23 easy miles of road.  This is a good test of your bikepacking equipment.
Continuous Teams that consist of 3 - 8 riders:  Everyone on each team starts and finishes together.  All team members roll through each feed station together.  To register a team, include each participant's name in the notes field when registering. Also supply a team name.

http://www.overlandbasecamp.cc/dusk-to-dawn-ride-2017/
notes:
Distance:  About 90-miles
Elevation Gain:  About 6,500 feet
Terrain:  Mixed.  60% dirt; 40% pavement
Geography:  Suburban and some urban
Territory:  From deep woods to well traveled roads
Sky:  Dark
http://www.overlandbasecamp.cc/dusk-to-dawn-ride-2017/
directions:
Ride Studio Cafe
1720 Massachusetts Ave
Lexington, MA 02420

title: Tour Opacum
description:
Explore the most beautiful backroads, rolling hills, and wooded forests that New England has to offer. Situated in the rolling uplands of central Massachusetts in the watersheds of the Quaboag and Quinebaug rivers, The Tour Opacum will provide an exploration of the most scenic roads that this region has to offer, while passing several of the properties that Opacum Land Trust has conserved along the way.  

Four different route options (100, 50, 25 and 7.5 miles) will provide riders of all abilities a great opportunity to get out and see this beautiful part of the state.  All of the routes start and end at Rapscallion Brewery, where a celebration of Land Conservation, including live music, food and craft beer will take place at the end of the ride. Fully stocked rest stops and SAG support will be offered on all routes. Visit RideWithGPS to view the routes.  A family-friendly route of approx 7.5 miles is also available, and will be clearly marked.
course:
Ride registration begins at 6:45, and 100 mile ride participants may depart on a rolling basis from 7:00 to 7:30am.  
•50 mile ride participants depart from 9:00 through 9:30am
•25 mile ride participants depart from 11:30am through 12:00
•7.5 mile family ride participants depart from 12:30 through 1:00pm
•The return time window for all riders is approximately: 1:30 to 2:00 and the after-ride party with the Tony Soul project begins at 2:00.

title: Jeremy Powers JAM Fund Grand Fundo
Goldberg Properties Gran Prix of Beverly Presented by Kelly Automotive
NEBRA August Adventure
description:
Join the New England Bicycle Racing Association for a mixed medium bicycle ride through beautiful Western Massachusetts. Riders have a choice of two routes, 45 miles or 75 miles departing South Deerfield and heading north over backroads, dirt roads and bike paths. On returning to Deerfield enjoy a post ride pizza party catered by Hillside Organic Pizza. 

Riders can choose to ride solo, in groups or you can join small organized groups led by prominent members of the New England Cycling community. All proceeds from the ride will benefit the New England Bicycle Racing Association to help fund administration and programming.
course: Riders have a choice of two routes, 45 miles or 75 miles departing South Deerfield and heading north over backroads, dirt roads and bike paths.
registration: The August Adventure costs $70 per adult, $20 for riders under 19 years of age. Registration includes the full day's activities, post ride meal and beverages and a NEBRA swag bag full of goodies. Sig up online using the official registration service of NEBRA at www.bikereg.com/augustadventure. Sign up by July 1st and take $15 off an adult entry fee! Save even more by becoming a NEBRA Supporting Member- learn more at http://www.bikereg.com/nebra-membership
notes:
The ride will begin and end at Douglas Auctioneers, 241 Greenfield Road, S. Deerfield MA 01373. We are advertising a 10am start, but you may roll out anytime from 9:30 onward. This is a self guided ride- we will provide cue sheets and the route will be marked with arrows, but unless you are joining one of the small groups there will be no ride leaders.

This is a ride not a race- the roads are open to traffic so please obey the rules of the road and be courteous to other road users and local residents. We encourage you to stop often and enjoy the wonderful scenery, read the historic markers and take pictures!

All riders must wear an approved helmet. The ride will cover a variety of rolling terrain. Cyclocross or gravel bikes will be the most comfortable, though experienced riders will be fine on a road bike with 25-28mm tires.

We will have roving support staff and there will be two aid stations, but please plan to be self sufficient with food, water, a pump and a spare tube or two.
directions: The ride will begin and end at Douglas Auctioneers, 241 Greenfield Road, S. Deerfield MA 01373.
